  19. ‌let err = Syntaxerr.ill_formed_ast

  21. ‌let empty_record loc = err loc "Records cannot be empty."
  22. ‌let invalid_tuple loc = err loc "Tuples must have at least 2 components."
  23. ‌let no_args loc = err loc "Function application with no argument."
  24. ‌let empty_let loc = err loc "Let with no bindings."
  25. ‌let empty_type loc = err loc "Type declarations cannot be empty."
  26. ‌let complex_id loc = err loc "Functor application not allowed here."
  27. ‌let module_type_substitution_missing_rhs loc =
  28.   err loc "Module type substitution with no right hand side"

  30. ‌let simple_longident id =
  31.   let rec is_simple = function
  32.     | Longident.Lident _ -> true
  33.     | Longident.Ldot (id, _) -> is_simple id
  34.     | Longident.Lapply _ -> false
  35.   in
  36.   if not (is_simple id.txt) then complex_id id.loc

  38. ‌let iterator =
  39.   let super = Ast_iterator.default_iterator in
  40.   let type_declaration self td =

  42.     let loc = td.ptype_loc in

  47.   let typ self ty =

  55.   in
  56.   let pat self pat =
  57.     begin match pat.ppat_desc with
  58.     | Ppat_construct (_, Some (_, ({ppat_desc = Ppat_tuple _} as p)))
  59.       when Builtin_attributes.explicit_arity pat.ppat_attributes ->
  60.         super.pat self p (* allow unary tuple, see GPR#523. *)
  61.     | _ ->
  62.         super.pat self pat
  63.     end;
  64.     let loc = pat.ppat_loc in
  65.     match pat.ppat_desc with
  66.     | Ppat_tuple ([] | [_]) -> invalid_tuple loc
  67.     | Ppat_record ([], _) -> empty_record loc
  68.     | Ppat_construct (id, _) -> simple_longident id
  69.     | Ppat_record (fields, _) ->
  70.       List.iter (fun (id, _) -> simple_longident id) fields
  71.     | _ -> ()
  72.   in
  73.   let expr self exp =

  75.     | Pexp_construct (_, Some ({pexp_desc = Pexp_tuple _} as e))

  77.         super.expr self e (* allow unary tuple, see GPR#523. *)
  78.     | _ ->
  79.         super.expr self exp
  80.     end;
  81.     let loc = exp.pexp_loc in
  82.     match exp.pexp_desc with
  83.     | Pexp_tuple ([] | [_]) -> invalid_tuple loc
  84.     | Pexp_record ([], _) -> empty_record loc
  85.     | Pexp_apply (_, []) -> no_args loc

  93.       List.iter (fun (id, _) -> simple_longident id) fields
